🧠 Introduction

MongoDB is one of the most popular NoSQL databases.

Unlike MySQL, MongoDB stores data in flexible JSON-like documents.

Python can interact with MongoDB to:

✔ Store documents
✔ Retrieve data
✔ Update records
✔ Delete records
✔ Build scalable applications

---

🔹 What is MongoDB?

```text id="mongodb_def"
MongoDB is a NoSQL document-oriented database that stores data in BSON (Binary JSON) format.
```

---

🎯 Why MongoDB?

✔ Flexible schema
✔ High performance
✔ Easy scalability
✔ JSON-like documents
✔ Widely used in modern applications

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

⚖️ MySQL vs MongoDB

| Feature | MySQL | MongoDB |
|----------|----------|----------|
| Database Type | Relational | NoSQL |
| Storage | Tables | Collections |
| Record | Row | Document |
| Schema | Fixed | Flexible |
| Query Language | SQL | MongoDB Query Language |

---

🏗️ MongoDB Structure

```text id="mongodb_structure"
Database
    ↓
Collection
    ↓
Document
```

---

📄 Example Document

```json id="mongodb_document"
