🏗️ Create Database

MongoDB automatically creates databases when data is inserted.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

💻 Example

```python id="create_database"
db = client["company"]
```

---

🗂️ Create Collection

Collections are similar to tables in SQL.

---

💻 Example

```python id="create_collection"
employees = db["employees"]
```

---

📥 Insert One Document

---

💻 Example

```python id="insert_one"
employee = {
    "name": "Saakshi",
    "salary": 50000,
    "department": "IT"
}

employees.insert_one(employee)
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="insert_one_output"
Document Inserted
```

---

📥 Insert Multiple Documents

---

💻 Example

```python id="insert_many"
data = [

    {
        "name": "Alex",
        "salary": 40000
    },

    {
        "name": "Emma",
        "salary": 60000
    },

    {
        "name": "John",
        "salary": 55000
    }

]

