📖 Retrieve Documents

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔹 Find All Documents

```python id="find_all"
for emp in employees.find():
    print(emp)
```

---

▶️ Sample Output

```text id="find_output"
{
 '_id': ObjectId(...),
 'name': 'Saakshi',
 'salary': 50000
}
```

---

🔹 Find One Document

```python id="find_one"
employee = employees.find_one(
    {"name": "Saakshi"}
)

print(employee)
```

---

🔍 Query Documents

---

💻 Example

```python id="query_docs"
for emp in employees.find(
    {"salary": {"$gt": 50000}}
):
    print(emp)
```

---

📌 MongoDB Operators

| Operator | Meaning |
|-----------|-----------|
| `$gt` | Greater than |
| `$lt` | Less than |
| `$gte` | Greater than or equal |
| `$lte` | Less than or equal |
| `$eq` | Equal |
| `$ne` | Not equal |

---

✏️ Update One Document

---

💻 Example

```python id="update_one"
employees.update_one(
    {"name": "Alex"},
    {
        "$set": {
            "salary": 70000
        }
    }
)
```

---

▶️ Result

```text id="update_result"
Document Updated
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

✏️ Update Multiple Documents

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

💻 Example

```python id="update_many"
employees.update_many(
    {},
    {
        "$set": {
            "status": "Active"
        }
    }
)
```

---

❌ Delete One Document

---

💻 Example

```python id="delete_one"
employees.delete_one(
    {"name": "Alex"}
)
```

---

❌ Delete Multiple Documents

---

💻 Example

```python id="delete_many"
employees.delete_many(
    {"salary": {"$lt": 30000}}
)
```

---

📊 Count Documents

---

💻 Example

```python id="count_docs"
count = employees.count_documents({})

print(count)
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="count_output"
5
```

---

📑 Sorting Documents

---

💻 Example

```python id="sort_docs"
for emp in employees.find().sort(
    "salary",
    -1
):
    print(emp)
```

---

📌 Sort Order

| Value | Order |
|---------|---------|
| `1` | Ascending |
| `-1` | Descending |

