🧠 Interview Answer (Simple)

> MongoDB is a NoSQL document database that stores data in JSON-like documents. Python interacts with MongoDB using the PyMongo library, allowing developers to perform CRUD operations efficiently while benefiting from MongoDB's flexible schema and scalability.

